content.body:
### Shop 255/35R19 Tire Size
The 255/35R19 is a low profile, sporty tire that comes on many of today’s sports cars, as well as many different luxury cars. SimpleTire offers several different options that can stand up to the high demand that drivers expect from their tires. 

Popular vehicles include:
2000-2006, 2009-2018 BMW M3
2009-2016 Mercedes-Benz E Class AMG
2015-2019 Subaru WRX STI
2015-2021 Audi S5
2018-2021 Kia Stinger

When you’re driving something as sporty and powerful as a Mercedes E Class AMG, you’re going to want the most grip without sacrificing comfort and quietness. That’s where the [Continental ExtremeContact DWS06 PLUS](https://simpletire.com/brands/continental-tires/extremecontact-dws06-plus) comes in to play. Built with Continental’s SPORTPLUS+ technology and up to a 50,000 mile tread life warranty, you can be ready for the road ahead.

If you’re more of an AWD enthusiast with an Audi S5 or Subaru WRX STI, then the [Toyo Proxes T1 Sport](https://simpletire.com/brands/toyo-tires/proxes-t1-sport) may be a better fit for you.These ultra-high-performance (UHP) tires offer an inside notched rib design for enhanced braking performance, as well as larger outer blocks for improved handling and steering response.

While having a performance tire is a good option for drivers who like to push their cars to the limits, there are still options for those who just want a dependable all-season tire. Take the [Yokohama Advan Sport A/S Plus](https://simpletire.com/brands/yokohama-tires/advan-sport-a-s-plus) for example, which features an all-season tread, extra-large shoulder blocks for improved turning performance, and up to a 55,000 tread life warranty, which makes the Advan Sport A/S Plus a great option for drivers who want the best of both worlds.

Whether you drive an Audi S5, Mercedes-Benz E Class AMG, Subaru WRX STI, or something else, SimpleTire has a set of 255/35R19 tires that meets your needs at a great price!
